 return of the jedi 
 iii 
 
 the sandstorm obscured breath thought motion the roar of italone was disorienting sounding like it came from everywhere at once as if theuniverse were composed of noise and this was its chaotic center 
 the seven heroes walked step by step through the murky gale holding on to oneanother so as not to get lost artoo was first following the signal of the homingdevice which sang to him in a language not garbled by the wind threepio camenext then leia guiding han and finally luke and lando supporting the hobblingwookiee 
 artoo beeped loudly and they all looked up vague dark shapes could be seenthrough the typhoon 
 i know shouted han all i can see is a lot of blowing sand 
 all any of us can see leia shouted back 
 then i guess getting better 
 for a few steps the dark shapes grew darker and then out of the darkness themillennium falcon appeared flanked by and a soon as the group huddled under the bulk of the falcon the wind died down tosomething more describable as a severe weather condition threepio hit a the gangplank lowered with a hum 
 solo turned to skywalker got to hand it to you kid you were pretty goodout there 
 luke shrugged it off i had a lot of help he started toward his 
 han stopped him his manner suddenly quieter even serious thanks forcoming after me luke 
 luke felt embarrassed for some reason he know how to respond toanything but a wisecrack from the old pirate think nothing of it he finally said 
 no thinkin a lot about it that carbon freeze was the closest thing todead there is and it just sleepin it was a big wide awake nothin 
 a nothing from which luke and the others had saved their own livesin great peril at his expense for no other reason than thathe was their friend thiswas a new idea for the cocky once terrible and wonderful there wasjeopardy in this turn of events it made him feel somehow blinder than before butvisionary as well it was confusing once he was alone now he was a part 
 that realization made him feel indebted a feeling always abhorred onlynow the debt was somehow a new kind of bond a bond of brotherhood it was evenfreeing in a strange way 
 he was no longer so alone 
